Storage Area networks are commonly used in Data centers to Provisions access to storage devices using block input/output (I/O) a San is isolated from the main network. It is only accessed by servers.

SAN has a mix of supporting stuff; like it can support RAID, tape libraries, etc. allowing for supported fabrics. It has a variety of fabrics. Can integrate different types of storage.

SAN Fabrics;

Fibre Channel; Uses Fiber cables but doesn't]’t rely on it. A SAN based on Fibrechannel Switched Fabric (FC-SW) Involves 3 main types of components;
Initiator; Servers with HBA (host Bus Adapter) jhas access to the SAN.
Target; A fabric. The Storage Device, can include; Raid ARRAYS, Tape drives and tape libraries, etc. They are divided into logical volumes and identified by LUNs.
LUN ; 64 Bit logical Unit Number
The initiator will use SCSI, SAS, SATA or NVMe commands to operate the storage devices in network, depending on which interface they support.
FC Switch; Provides the connection between initiator and targets. High performance FC switches are often referred to as directors. 

Fibre channels can use rates from 1GFC (1 Gbps) up to 128 GFC. Fibre Channel uses dedicated SFP+ and QSFP and twinax modular transceivers. Fibrechannels are ethernet transceivers can’t match.

The intiators and targets are identified by 64 bit WorldWide Names (WWN) Similar to network adapter MAC address. Initators and targets are allocated their own WWN, referred to as WWNN. also each port on them can have its own WWPN
WWN; Uniquely identify initators or targets
WWPN; Ports can also have identifiers!
WWNN; WWN allocated.

