Methods for encapsulating;
PPP; Used serial communications to encapsulate, meaning it Encapsulates on Data Link Layer, common for WAN Links and older dial up connections.

GRE; Encapsulates IP Packets. When moved around next hop routers it is in L2, the routers only looks at  Outer GRE, until it’s finally on destination Router. And then decapsulates it.
Outer GRE; A packet  that has Ip src and IP Header.
IP Security; Internet Protocol Security (IPSec) also operates at the Network layer of the OSI model to authenticate hosts and encrypt packets. IPSec is used with other protocols to provide connection security, and it is increasingly used as a standalone VPN protocol.
TLS/DTLS; Another encapsulating method, but can add extra overhead because it already works on Session Layer.

AH; Authenticates and Integrity by calculating ICV (making sure the payload has not been modified) 
ESP; Encrypts the entire payload. Has header, trailer (extra padding for cryptography) and ICV Unlike AH, ESP excludes IP header when calculating ICV.

! With ESP, algorithms for both confidentiality (symmetric cipher) and authentication/integrity (hash function) are usually applied together. It is possible to use one or the other

IPSec Two Modes;
Transport; IP headers not encrypted, just payload.
Tunnel; payload encrypted and IP header is hidden to, is encapsulated as datagram with new IP header.

IKE; Authenticates before using AH or ESP. 
Two phases of IKE; 
Phase 1; Establishes identity of two peers and performs key agreement. Using diffie-helman algorithm to make secure channel
Two methods of authenticating peers; 
Digital certificates; mutually trusted certificate authority to identify one another
PSK; Passphrase
Phase 2; Uses secure channel created in phase 1 to establish which ciphers and key sizes will be used with AH and/ESP in IP sec session.

Two Version of IKE:
IKE Version 1; for site-to-site and host-to-host topologies and requires a supporting protocol to implement remote access VPNS.
IKEv2; Has additional features that have made the protocol popular for use as stand alone remote access client-to-Site VPN solutions. The main changes are following;
-Support EAP, ex; user authentication against a RADIUS server.
-Provides a simple setup mode that reduces bandwidth without compromising security
-Allow for NAT and MOBIKE multihoming
Multihoming means that a smartphone client with Wi-Fi and cellular interfaces can keep the IPsec connection alive when switching between them.
MOBIKE = Mobility and Multihoming Protocol It’s an extension to IKEv2 that lets an IPsec VPN survive IP address changes.
L2TP; L2TP is a Layer 2 tunneling protocol used to carry PPP frames over an IP network.
